540:   into the DRAM unless there is an active DRAM read in process. 
541:   
542:   We turn on out only if we are in a DRAM cycle, and it is a CPU read (CPU_RW == 1).
543:   NOTE that DRAM_CS is alreay gated by /AS in the decode CPLS, so this can't accidently drive
544:   the data bus unless we are in an actual DRAM memory cycle, and it is a read operation.
545:   The bus drivers for the DRAM have the OE signals always asserted, so flipping direction is 
546:   what prevents driving of the data bus as the wrong time.  This was done to speed up the data
547:   signal.
548:*/
549:
550:DRAM_DATA_DIR = !DRAM_CS & CPU_RW;
